At the same time in Belarus women do agree on most issues related to abortion: they think that women have a right to make abortion decision themselves ^ 53 . Historically, the abortion remained an act of deep private significance for women; it was an element of strong private life. Men were not involved into discussion with wives on this topic; opinion of a male partner was not a reason to take or not to take the decision on abortion. In Belarus there still exist stereotypes denying that abortion is the right decision of self-defending woman in a case of incestuous family.
Today a major part of women declare their readiness to use qualified medical services^ 54 . Nevertheless, many women seem ashamed of having such requests for medical support. Women afraid of a possible social stigmatization and low status separation for having such needs. Results of other surveys can also be used to emphasize a hidden need among women of obtaining medical services for abortion at early priming stages before a medical termination action induction is complicated and becomes the reason of necessitating admission to a maternity hospital.
